>From: Dean Goodmanson [mailto:goodmansond(-at-)gmail.com]

>> its the straps when you lift the top up that run from top of canvas to
>bottom of canvas and are stretchy like...?
>
>Mine are blown too.     They're 10+ ft. long fabric wrapped bungee
>cord and I haven't seen them in Farm and Fleet style stores.

Larger marine chandleries (Defender.com, WestMarine.com) stock a nylon web
tubing and various diameters of bungee cord. Maybe you could make some? For
a really high-tech look, cover the bungee with one of these single braid
lines:
http://www.samsonrope.com/home/newrecmarine/compgraderunningrigging.cfm
(the top four). It'll look like a braided spring as it contracts.

